100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 17, 1925, the world was abuzz with significant events. In the United States, the trial of John T. Scopes, known as the "Scopes Monkey Trial," continued to draw nationwide attention as it pitted science against religion in a landmark case over teaching evolution in schools. Meanwhile, in Europe, the Locarno Treaties were being discussed, aiming to secure peace and stability in post-World War I Europe. In the Soviet Union, reports surfaced of continuing agricultural reforms, as the government pushed for the collectivization of farms.
